Three Objectives

All data was collected on August 6, 2025 using a DJI Mini 4 Pro at 40â€“120 m altitude with pre-planned grid and circular flight paths.

1
Surface Temperature Analysis
Used thermal drone imagery to map surface temperature distribution across different land cover types â€” grassland, forest, and pavement â€” across the full UTM campus.

Vegetation Change Detection
Compared drone RGB imagery from July 2024 and August 2025 at the Principal's Field â€” an open grassland with diverse forest components selected for its vegetation variability.
ğŸŒ¿ Vegetation coverage remained stable between 2024 and 2025 â€” minimal impervious surface expansion detected.
3

Generated a 3D model of the Maanjiwe Nendamowinan (MN) building from 42 drone images using Structure-from-Motion photogrammetry in 3DF Zephyr, then processed in ArcGIS Pro.
